%% This little package provides a `cheap solution' to customize the
%% math fonts used in a LaTeX document.  You can either use it with the
%% `upright' option to get upright letters in maths or with the `generic'
%% option to get math italic letters from the default text font. If you
%% intend to use scalable outline fonts without optical scaling (as usual
%% PS fonts) you will need the `psscale' option if you hope to read the
%% scriptscriptsize'd letters. [The default  is generic + psscale]
%% WARNING: NEVER TRUST THIS PACKAGE !
%% In fact, it makes use of *text* fonts for *maths* and TeX treats these
%% kind of beasts in rather different manners, for instance, kerning  and
%% side-bearings won't be right, so use this only for simple
%% formulas, and always check carefully the output: many formulae could
%% need explicit (m)kerns to work correctly (the product $fi$ for instance
%% *should* be put as (more or less) $f\mkern3mui$ ).

